{"tree":{"type":"node","kind":"SOURCE_FILE","width":23,"children":[{"type":"node","kind":"LET_BINDING","width":23,"children":[{"type":"token","kind":"IDENT_EXPR","text":"let","width":3},{"type":"token","kind":"WHITESPACE","text":" ","width":1},{"type":"node","kind":"PAREN_PATTERN","width":2,"children":[{"type":"token","kind":"IDENT_EXPR","text":"(","width":1},{"type":"node","kind":"ERROR","width":0,"children":[]},{"type":"token","kind":"IDENT_EXPR","text":"`","width":1}]},{"type":"token","kind":"IDENT_EXPR","text":"`","width":1},{"type":"token","kind":"IDENT_EXPR","text":"Tag","width":3},{"type":"token","kind":"WHITESPACE","text":" ","width":1},{"type":"token","kind":"IDENT_EXPR","text":"x","width":1},{"type":"token","kind":"IDENT_EXPR","text":")","width":1},{"type":"token","kind":"WHITESPACE","text":" ","width":1},{"type":"token","kind":"IDENT_EXPR","text":"=","width":1},{"type":"token","kind":"WHITESPACE","text":" ","width":1},{"type":"node","kind":"IDENT_EXPR","width":7,"children":[{"type":"token","kind":"IDENT_EXPR","text":"variant","width":7}]}]}]},"diagnostics":[{"kind":{"id":"E0007","name":"invalid-pattern","expected":"identifier or pattern","found":{"kind":"`","text":"`"},"fix":"add a variable name, \"_\" (underscore) to ignore it.","hint":"\nThe left side of a let-expression allows you to pattern match on values to assign them to variables, but also to deconstruct them and access their inner values.\n\n   ```ocaml\n   let variable = 42 in\n   let { x; _ } = point in\n   let Some x = optional in\n   (* ... *)\n   ```\n\nBeware that pattern matching on only one of many possible values will lead to runtime errors!\n"},"span":{"start":5,"end":5}},{"kind":{"id":"E0003","name":"missing-let-binding-equals","expected":"=","found":{"kind":"`","text":"`"},"fix":"add = between the pattern and expression","hint":"Every let binding needs an = between the pattern and the expression."},"span":{"start":5,"end":5}}]}
